snippet.textDisplay: Faced with having to play three games anyway ...I was sort a rooting for a 49ers win...as Seattle seems to play much better on the road and would have to play the Eagles(instead of the vikings), who are suffering greatly with injured personnel. DIggs and Brown back by the time the divisional round against the 49ers. On the other hand, the 49ers having a fifth seed would have been worth it. But this was a great and exciting game...after having a miserable first half...they rebounded and Lynch got some clutch plays. Impressed by 49ers defense defending the goal line on both the seattle catches ...guess they practiced that a lot after the falcons loss....but still, it would give me pause if I were a 49ers fan.
